HEADWORD: Tikor
<hw>Tik"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>tikhur</ets>.]</ety> <def>A starch or arrow-root made from the
tubes of an East Indian zinziberaceous plant (<spn>Curcuma
angustifolia</spn>); also, the plant itself.</def>⟦br⟧
